Local Enviroment Setup & Laravel Installation

1 .xampp
2. git bash

3. composer

https://getcomposer.org/download/

click composer-Setup.exe
do not select developer mode, which will give us full download


open git bash in htdocs
type: composer
you should be able to see all composer commands

First, download the Laravel installer using Composer:

https://laravel.com/docs/5.8/installation

composer global require laravel/installer 


composer create-project --prefer-dist laravel/laravel blog


check in localhost after installation

http://localhost:8080/blog/public/


check migration
php aritsan migrate

app/provider/appserviceprovider

use Illuminate\Support\Facades\Schema;
under boot method
Schema::defaultStringLength(191);

php artisan make:auth


change .env which 




echo "# curd" >> README.md
